Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
12075 E 45th Ave is currently 60% leased with nearly all major building infrastructure items taken care of by the current ownership group, creating value-add potential for an Investor. Major infrastructure items addressed by the current ownership include a costly elevator modernization, parking lot resurface/remill and a lobby remodel. The suites and some common areas could use some refreshing in order to drive increased rental rates, but building infrastructure is in excellent condition.

An Office User Buyer will be able to immediately occupy vacant space, take advantage of the onsite amenities/retail and the strong parking ratio. Since most of the major infrastructure items have been addressed by current ownership, a User will be able to spend any needed additional capital expenses on cosmetic upgrades to the suites and/or building.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to offer the Historic Crawford Hill Mansion for sale, located in Denver’s exclusive Capitol Hill submarket. Just a few blocks south of the Colorado State Capitol Building, the property offers the standalone building and a gated parking lot with the opportunity to be redeveloped. Price of the property which must be sold together is $7,250,000 delineated as $5.7M for the mansion and $1.55M for the parcel at 933 N. Sherman.

Built in 1906, the Crawford Hill Mansion is a distinctive property of French Renaissance Revival-style that is rich in history, architectural significance and allure. As one of the largest residences built in Denver at the time, the building exudes opulence with a large ballroom, grand dining room and a two-level foyer with a grand staircase. The current owners have elegantly restored the property and brought it into the 21st century, leasing it as an attorney’s office for about 25 employees. The Mansion has been placed on the National Register of Historic Places which will preserve the exterior so that it remains untouched on the outside.

The property consists of 19,005 sq. ft. of office space in three levels, as well as a finished basement area that contains 1200 sq. ft. The structure itself is brick and is topped by a tile roof with copper flashing's and gutters. The exterior displays intricate designs and touches with exquisite moldings, pediments and Corinthian columns—giving the Mansion a powerful presence on 10th Avenue and Sherman Street. The property also has a covered porch, in-ground swimming pool, deck/pergola on the west side of the rear lot with gas fire pit, and a gated parking lot for 28 vehicles which is a separate city parcel. There are two staircases that access all three above-ground levels and one grand staircase that connects the first and second level of the property. There is an elevator that services the first, second and third levels. With two large conference rooms, a reception area, kitchen, break area and numerous offices, the property efficiently serves the attorneys and staff that currently occupy the building.
